Task Load Index
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The NASA Task Load Index (NASA-TLX) is a widely used, subjective, multidimensional assessment tool that rates perceived 
workload in order to assess a task, system, or team's effectiveness or other aspects of performance.

Step 1 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Rate how demanding the different factors seemed for your task on a scale from 0 to 100.

Step 2 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Which factor influenced your work more?
Rate for each pair.

Step 3 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Look at the results. AVG value shows, how demanding the task was overall.
The export button exports the results as a TXT-File in the folder from which you started the application.